<taxonomicNameLabel box="[811,905,1100,1125]" pageId="41" pageNumber="442" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[811,905,1100,1125]" pageId="41" pageNumber="442">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1153,1100,1125]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planidorsum">
<emphasis box="[972,1153,1100,1125]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="442">H. planidorsum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the middle lobe of mesoscutum rather flat and slightly protuberant (convex and moderately protuberant in 
<taxonomicName box="[1199,1372,1135,1160]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachygena">
<emphasis box="[1199,1372,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="442">H. brachygena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the propodeal medial areola is wide (
<figureCitation box="[557,644,1172,1197]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1892,1914]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,697,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[340,1247,697,1871]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 21. Wroughtonia planidorsum (Watanabe), â™€, China. A, wings; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, first and second metasomal tergites, dorsal aspect; D, hind femur and tibia, lateral aspect; E, propodeum, medio-dorsal aspect; F, habitus, lateral aspect; G, head, lateral aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, mesosoma, dorsal aspect." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827568/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="442">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
E; narrower in 
<taxonomicName box="[832,1004,1172,1197]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Wroughtonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="442" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachygena">
<emphasis box="[832,1004,1172,1197]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="442">H. brachygena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
